issue.title: Add an option for specifying max number of concurrent seeding torrent
issue.body:
<!-- DO NOT POST LINKS OR REFERENCES TO COPYRIGHTED CONTENT IN YOUR ISSUE. -->

**What version of WebTorrent Desktop are you using?**
0.24.0

**What operating system and version?**
win10

**What problem do you want to solve?**
seeding old torrent or having to manually pause a torrent
bittorrentweb has this
![image](https://github.com/webtorrent/webtorrent-desktop/assets/26696482/2bfefe4d-9c21-431e-b05e-1df9ddb892ed)


**What do you think is the correct solution to this problem?**
and unsigned int option in settings to specify max number of seeds ( 0 means no seeding )
or
an option to to not seed ever ( i have metered connection and my isp counts every freaking bit )

**Are you willing to submit a pull request to implement this change?**
